author: Russell Brand
description:
Trial by jury is under threat in the UK, with proposed reforms pushing AI, judge-only trials, and incentives to plead guilty early—effectively reshaping the justice system. Russell explores how these changes align with a wider trend of censorship, surveillance, and centralized control. Is this about fixing a backlog—or about consolidating power?

Today we're finishing our watch of ‘Unlawful Killing’, the explosive Diana documentary by Keith Allen that was effectively buried due to its allegations of a royal cover-up. As the film ramps up its claims, we dive deeper into the evidence, the medical timeline, and the voices who say Diana’s death was no accident. What does the second half reveal—and why was this too much for UK audiences to see?
